track_notes: Parking on roadside just south east of the bridge at Braidlie Farm. A straight forward route from there up to Greatmoor Hill (86 mins). Easy navigation to Cauldcleuch Head by following the fence up windy edge (60 mins). Quad and sheep tracks apparent. Return over Muckle Land Knowe. It was a little tussocky down to 400m and then good surfaces thereafter. I recommend this route. (SS-106 back to car 82 mins). The Braidley Burn needs to be forded both ways but water was well below boot height in Feb 2016. If you go to activate SS-106 please tip me off via e-mail (See QRZ.COM) as I need to SOTA Complete this summit as a chaser.
track_title: A heart shaped route over SS-106 and SS-114

track_notes:
This is a there and back, the hardest part of route finding is locating the fire break in the forest. The rest of the route is fence following.

This route has a bit less ascent because it starts at the summit of the Waverly line. However you do visit Greatmoor Hill GM/SS-114 twice.

Walk time for me was about 5:30 and the day was nearly 10 hours.
track_title: There and back GM/SS-114 and GM/SS-106 from Whitrope Railway centre
